1. tensorflow
*     $sudo apt-get install python-pip python-dev
*     $sudo apt-get install python-sklearn
*     $pip install opencv-python
*     $sudo pip install tensorflow   #must check which is desired:cpu or if gpu, then install tensorflow_gpu
*     $sudo -E pip install imutils
*     $sudo -E pip install --upgrade scipy

if 'sudo -E pip install tensorflow' is entered, the most latest version will be installed)

1.1 how to upgrade tensorflow: 
*     $sudo pip uninstall protobuf
*     $sudo pip uninstall tensorflow
*     $sudo pip install --upgrade https: // .....look up address for desired version
1.2  how to uninstall tf
*     $sudo pip uninstall tensorflow

2. keras + tf for bg
*     $sudo apt-get install python-dev            #scipy included?
*     $sudo apt-get install python-pip
*     $sudo apt-get install python-opencv
*     $sudo -E apt-get install libhdf5-dev 
*     $sudo -E apt-get install cython 
*     $sudo apt-get install python-h5py
*     $sudo -E pip install keras( if installed wrong version, type 'pip uninstall keras' to uninstall)
*     $sudo -E pip install tflearn 
*     $sudo pip install scikit-learn
*     $sudo pip install imutils

2.1 install keras with specific version
*     $sudo pip install keras==1.2.2
*     $sudo pip install tensorflow        #numpy included


2.2 install keras for training c3d #sudo chown -R $USER /usr/local/lib/python2.7 to enable access
#keras version installed keras-2.1.5 (2.0.0 bu xing)
*     $pip install keras
*     $apt-get install libhdf5-dev -y
*     $apt-get install python-h5py -y
3. pip
how to upgrade pip
*     $pip install --upgrade pip       #(bu neng jia sudo)

